{"summary":"All six amendments identify real consistency or robustness problems in milestone task-run completion. Several overlap around the same root issue: completion is currently split across append-style lineage writes and update-style rewrites, leaving snapshot/journal synchronization, per-run identity, and concurrent safety underdefined.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-1-83cc18bd","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real state-consistency bug. The public service helper for completing a run only rewrites task-runs.ndjson, but completion also needs to clear active_bead, adjust progress counters, and append the corresponding journal event. Whether that is done by expanding update_task_run or by folding callers into one completion path, snapshot and journal state cannot be left stale."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-b88127a5","decision":"accept","rationale":"`Skipped` is a distinct terminal outcome, so recording it as `BeadFailed` is semantically wrong and will mislead operators and downstream consumers. The aggregate-progress treatment of skipped runs also needs an explicit policy; today they disappear from the counters while still ending the active run, which is not a robust or self-explanatory state model."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-931e3b47","decision":"accept","rationale":"The API contract is currently ambiguous. One public path appends a second completion row while the other mutates the existing row, and there is no documentation or regression test defining which semantics callers should rely on. Even if the eventual fix is to collapse to a single path, this ambiguity is a maintainability defect that should be made explicit and covered by tests."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-6940a2a3","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a legitimate lost-update hazard. `update_task_run` does a whole-file read/modify/write, so a concurrent append between the read and rewrite can be silently discarded. Atomic rename only protects the final replacement, not the read-modify-write window. The limitation should at least be documented, and proper locking would be the stronger fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-3c001aa9","decision":"accept","rationale":"This identifies the core design inconsistency. `task-runs.ndjson` is described as lineage, not an event log, so leaving a stale `Running` row and appending a second terminal row for the same attempt is a poor completion model; meanwhile the mutate-in-place helper leaves snapshot and journal state stale. Consolidating completion into one path that updates snapshot/journal and finalizes the existing run entry is the most maintainable resolution."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-15b667eb","decision":"accept","rationale":"Matching only on `bead_id` plus `project_id` is no longer sufficient once `run_id` exists for per-run auditability. A single project can legitimately have multiple runs for the same bead, so updating the last matching row can rewrite the wrong attempt. The update path should use `run_id` when available and reject ambiguous matches instead of guessing."}]}